Package: mnlfa
Type: Package
Title: Moderated Nonlinear Factor Analysis (MNLFA)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Matthias", "Ziegler",
    email = "matthias.ziegler@hu-berlin.de",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9373-0365"))
Description: Implements the stepwise Moderated Nonlinear Factor Analysis
    (MNLFA) procedure for assessing measurement invariance across observed
    moderator variables. Supports multidimensional measurement models with
    multiple latent variables (facets) per domain, which is a key advantage
    over existing implementations. The package builds moderated SEM syntax,
    fits models via the OpenMx backend through the mxsem interface, extracts
    significant moderations, selects anchor items, assembles full domain
    models, and computes person-specific parameter estimates.
    References: Bauer (2017) <doi:10.1080/00273171.2016.1256260>;
    Gottfredson et al. (2019) <doi:10.1037/met0000193>;
    Kolbe et al. (2022) <doi:10.1080/10705511.2021.1984772>.
